@baseUrl = http://localhost:4004
@email = admin@test.com
@password = admin123

### 1. Health check (no auth needed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Login — copy the accessToken from response into @token below
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 3. Set your token here after login
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VySWQiOiJ1c2VyLTEiLCJyb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJpYXQiOjE3ODExMTQxNDgsImV4cCI6MTc4MTExNzc0OH0.c9bq9dYiw2jw3PJyIP2nJmAnEJUcHOyKzL-IawvcIWQ

### 4. Hit protected route with valid token
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Hit protected route with no token — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile

### 6. Hit protected route with garbage token — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer thisisnotavalidtoken

### 7. Hit unknown route — expect 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/unknown/route

### 8. Hit public route (no auth) — expect proxy attempt
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/something

### 9. Login as regular user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@test.com",
  "password": "user123"
}

### 10. Set user token
@userToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VySWQiOiJ1c2VyLTIiLCJyb2xlIjoidXNlciIsImlhdCI6MTc4MTAyMTkzMSwiZXhwIjoxNzgxMDI1NTMxfQ.Pn-Wz6LaY6UlLkrZ859Mb0SGa41QdXDYmqe3X92-Y4o

### 11. Hit admin route as regular user — expect 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 12. Hit admin route as admin — expect 502 (no upstream, but auth passed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 13. Health check after DB routes loaded
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 14. Protected route — should still work same as before
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 15. Check rate limit headers are present
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 16. Check circuit breaker status
GET {{baseUrl}}/health/circuits

### 17. Spam a dead upstream — watch it go open after 5 failures
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 18. Health check shows redis connected
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 19. Hit API key protected route with valid key
GET {{baseUrl}}/billing/invoices
x-api-key: test-api-key-billing-service

### 20. Hit API key route with no key — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/billing/invoices

### 21. Hit API key route with wrong key — expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/billing/invoices
x-api-key: wrong-key

### 22. Check Prometheus metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics

### 23. First request — expect X-Cache: MISS
GET {{baseUrl}}/billing/invoices
x-api-key: test-api-key-billing-service

### 24. Second request — expect X-Cache: HIT (no upstream hit)
GET {{baseUrl}}/billing/invoices
x-api-key: test-api-key-billing-service

### 25. Check cache hit counter in metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics